es © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Greville II was born about 1300, in Burmington, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William de Greville I. He married Lucy of Warwickshire about 1321, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 1338."},"et":{"about 1300–Bef 1338":"umbes 1300–enne 1338","1300–1338":"1300–1338","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1322–1390":"1322–1390","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1338":"1338","1322":"1322","1300":"1300","about 1321":"umbes 1321","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1270":"1270","1390":"1390","Bef 1338":"enne 1338","Burmington, Shipston on Stour, Warwickshire, England":"Burmington, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burmington, Warwickshire, England":"Burmington, Warwickshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1300–Bef 1338":"noin 1300–ennen vuotta 1338","1300–1338":"1300–1338","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1322–1390":"1322–1390","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1338":"1338","1322":"1322","1300":"1300","about 1321":"noin 1321","about 1300":"noin 1300","1270":"1270","1390":"1390","Bef 1338":"ennen vuotta 1338","Burmington, Shipston on Stour, Warwickshire, England":"Burmington, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Burmington, Warwickshire, England":"Burmington, Warwickshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{